=\"HollywoodNewDisney\" />\n*''[[Beastie Boys Story]]'' \u2013 [[IMAX]] release on April 3, 2020 cancelled and to be released on [[Apple TV+]] on April 24.<ref name=\"DeadlineBeastie\" />\n*''[[Endings, Beginnings]]'' \u2013 Theatrical release cancelled and to be released on [[Video on Demand|VOD]] on April 17, 2020, with a [[HBO]] release on a yet-to-be determined date.\n*''[[Enter the Fat Dragon (2020 film)|Enter the Fat Dragon]]'' \u2013 Premiered online.{{efn|Except in the Philippines, where the film had already gone to theaters on January 29, 2020, before the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines|COVID-19 arrival in the country]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/RealityEntPH/status/1222323823380353025|title=The fat dragon is finally here! You can now watch Enter The Fat Dragon in cinemas near you. #EnterTheFatDragon #ThisIsREALITY|author=Reality Entertainment|date=January 28, 2020|access-date=March 14, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130060946/https://twitter.com/RealityEntPH/status/1222323823380353025|archive-date=January 30, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n*''[[Lost in Russia]]'' \u2013 Theatrical release cancelled and released on [[TikTok]], [[Toutiao]], Xigua on January 25, 2020 for free.<ref>{{cite news |author1=Patrick Frater |title=China\u2019s \u2018Lost in Russia\u2019 Switches to Unprecedented Online Release in Response to Coronavirus Outbreak |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/asia/coronavirus-china-lost-in-russia-online-release-1203478139/ |accessdate=25 January 2020 |work=variety |date=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n*''[[The Lovebirds (2020 film)|The Lovebirds]]'' \u2013 Theatrical release cancelled and to be released on [[Netflix]] on a yet-to-be determined date.<ref name=\"DeadlineLovebirds\" />\n*''[[My Spy]]'' \u2013 Theatrical release in the U.S. cancelled and to be released on [[Prime Video|Amazon Prime Video]] on a yet to-be determined date.<ref>{{cite web|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|url=https://deadline.com/2020/04/my-spy-acquired-by-amazon-studios-stx-dave-bautista-1202903723/|title=\u2018My Spy\u2019: STX Dave Bautista Action Comedy Acquired By Amazon Studios For Streaming|date=April 8, 2020 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> \n* ''[[Steven Universe: The Movie]]'' \u2013 This film's [[Fathom Events]] release on March 23, 2020 was cancelled after theaters across the country closed as a precautionary measure.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Harrigan |first1=Will |title=Fathom Events Cancels and Postpones Movies Due To Coronavirus |url=https://cosmicbook.news/fathom-events-cancel-postpones-coronavirus |website=Cosmic Book News |accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> The episode of ''[[Steven Universe Future]]'' that was supposed to play after this screening, \"Homeworld Bound\", showed up on [[Cartoon Network]]'s website the day the event was to take place.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Murphy |first1=Jackson |title=Rebecca Sugar Discusses the Final \u201cSteven Universe Future\u201d |url=http://www.animationscoop.com/rebecca-sugar-discusses-the-final-steven-universe-future/ |website=Animation Scoop |accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n*''[[Time to Hunt (film)|Time to Hunt]]'' \u2013 Theatrical release cancelled. Originally to have been released on Netflix on April 10, 2020,<ref>{{cite web|first=Yeon-soo|last=Kwak|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/03/689_286633.html|title='Time to Hunt' skips theaters and goes straight to Netflix|date=March 23, 2020|website=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324084152/https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/03/689_286633.html|archive-date=March 24, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> the streaming service's debut of the film was itself postponed two days earlier to comply with a ruling in the Seoul Central District Court regarding distribution contracts.<ref>{{cite web|first=Gyu-lee|last=Lee|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/04/689_287636.html|title=Netflix halts 'Time to Hunt' release, promotion after injunction|date=April 9, 2020|website=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n*''[[Trolls World Tour]]'' \u2013 Released  on VOD on April 6, 2020 in Europe and released simultaneously in theaters and on VOD  on April 10, 2020 in the United States.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fuster |first1=Jeremy |title=Universal to Release 'Trolls World Tour' for Digital Rental on Same Day as Theatrical Release |url=https://www.thewrap.com/universal-to-release-trolls-world-tour-for-digital-rental-on-same-day-as-theatrical-release/ |accessdate=March 16, 2020 |work=[[TheWrap]] |date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317184238/https://www.thewrap.com/universal-to-release-trolls-world-tour-for-digital-rental-on-same-day-as-theatrical-release/ |archive-date=March 17, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Ravindran |first1=Manori |title=Rakuten TV to Stream 'Trolls World Tour' in Europe Ahead of U.S. |url=https://variety.com/2020/biz/box-office/rakuten-tv-to-stream-trolls-world-tour-in-europe-ahead-of-u-s-1234570121/ |accessdate=April 4, 2020 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=April 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403134807/https://variety.com/2020/biz/box-office/rakuten-tv-to-stream-trolls-world-tour-in-europe-ahead-of-u-s-1234570121/ |archive-date=April 3, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Rubin |first1=Rebecca |title=\u2018Trolls World Tour\u2019 Straight to Streaming \u2014 Sign of the Times or the New Normal? |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/trolls-world-tour-streaming-theatrical-window-future-1234573263/ |accessdate=April 9, 2020 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Delayed ===\n<!-- Please insert in alphabetical order! Thanks! -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ffdead;\"\n! Film \n! Original release date\n! New release date or action taken\n|-\n|''[[Antebellum (film)|Antebe